      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. From the existing decision table, create a temporary working table `J09A_temp` and copy into it all rows where the tour identifier starts with `J09A`.\\n\\n2. In `J09A_temp`, add a new text column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` (initially empty for all rows).\\n\\n3. Classify meter reading type in `J09A_temp`:\\n   - For each `HAUS`, count how many `EQUNR` it has.\\n   - If a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"KSA\\\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`.\\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"EVU\\\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`.\\n\\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with table `EABLG` using column `INSTALLATION`, and update the working table with the joined result.\\n\\n5. Join the working table with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using column `EQUNR` (“JOIN table with NET_MASTER and SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR”), so that each record contains both sales customer data and net master data where available.\\n\\n6. For each record, compare the customer data from `SALES_MASTER` with the customer data from `NET_MASTER` and determine whether sales customer data for that record is present (i.e., not empty).\\n\\n7. For each record in the working table, decide which customer data to use:\\n   if sales customer data is NOT empty for this record:\\n       - Use the sales customer data table entries for this record (populate all customer-related fields from `SALES_MASTER`).\\n   else:\\n       - Use the net data customer table entries for this record (populate those fields from `NET_MASTER`).\\n\\n8. Export the resulting final table to a CSV file named `J09A`, using exactly these column names (and in this order) when writing the file:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n   Store the full path to the created CSV file in a variable `file_path` with value `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file located at `file_path` attached (use `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>` as the attachment location).\\n\\n10. After the email has been sent successfully, delete the temporary table `J09A_temp` from the database.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_3f112f09-7380-4988-8eae-77277d052d27"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "716c81d1-3a7c-4298-a3f4-158e9c42d116",
        "tool_call_id": "call_HBFHWdvHImKQHSWDTZXRWAnr",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. From the existing decision table, create a temporary working table `J09A_temp` and copy into it all rows where the tour identifier starts with `J09A`.\n\n2. In `J09A_temp`, add a new text column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` (initially empty for all rows).\n\n3. Classify meter reading type in `J09A_temp`:\n   - For each `HAUS`, count how many `EQUNR` it has.\n   - If a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"KSA\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`.\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"EVU\"` for all rows of that `HAUS`.\n\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with table `EABLG` using column `INSTALLATION`, and update the working table with the joined result.\n\n5. Join the working table with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using column `EQUNR` (“JOIN table with NET_MASTER and SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR”), so that each record contains both sales customer data and net master data where available.\n\n6. For each record, compare the customer data from `SALES_MASTER` with the customer data from `NET_MASTER` and determine whether sales customer data for that record is present (i.e., not empty).\n\n7. For each record in the working table, decide which customer data to use:\n   if sales customer data is NOT empty for this record:\n       - Use the sales customer data table entries for this record (populate all customer-related fields from `SALES_MASTER`).\n   else:\n       - Use the net data customer table entries for this record (populate those fields from `NET_MASTER`).\n\n8. Export the resulting final table to a CSV file named `J09A`, using exactly these column names (and in this order) when writing the file:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n   Store the full path to the created CSV file in a variable `file_path` with value `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file located at `file_path` attached (use `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>` as the attachment location).\n\n10. After the email has been sent successfully, delete the temporary table `J09A_temp` from the database.\n\n11. End the process."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
